<item>
            <title>[LU-558] lctl pool_list: Lustre filesystem &apos;lustre&apos; not found: No such file or directory (2)</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-558</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;On a configuration with a dedicated MGS hosting only the MGS but no MDT or clients, tests that invoke &quot;lctl pool_list&quot; on the &quot;mgs&quot; facet will fail.  For example,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;== sanity test 201c: Remove a pool =================================================================== 21:14:28 (1311912868)
client-4-ib: Pool lustre.cea1 not found
client-4-ib: Can&apos;t verify pool command since there is no local MDT or client, proceeding anyhow...
Waiting 90 secs for update
Updated after 5 sec: wanted &apos;foo&apos; got &apos;foo&apos;
Resetting fail_loc on all nodes...done.
PASS 201c (8s)
client-4-ib: Lustre filesystem &apos;lustre&apos; not found: No such file or directory (2)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The tests should either start a client on the MGS or use the MDS instead.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>A separate MGS device hosted on a dedicated MGS.</environment>
